The paper discusses predictive process monitoring, which involves making predictions about the future state of ongoing cases of a business process based on their incomplete execution traces and logs of historical traces. This problem is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves developing methods to make predictions. The paper also discusses the evaluation of these methods, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of security and privacy in predictive process monitoring, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CR). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DB, and cs.CR.
